commit.message:
Only use Ubuntu Trusty 14.04 for old Ruby versions

Given that most Ruby versions are supported by the default Ubuntu
distribution, Xenial 16.04, it seems better to use that for all the Ruby
versions that we can.

commit.message:
Don't use the new bundler v2 in builds

This requires Ruby v2.3 or higher which means that a bunch of our builds
fail. Ideally we'd use bundler v2 for more recent versions of Ruby, but
this will do for now.

Specify exact version of JRuby to use on Travis CI

In an attempt to fix broken JRuby builds as per this recommendation [1].

[1]: https://github.com/travis-ci/travis-ci/issues/8446#issuecomment-330180595
